{"title_page": "Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)", "text_new": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name                 = Ministry of Finance\n| native_name          = {{lang-nl|Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn}}\n| type                 = Department\n| logo                 = Logo-ministerie-van-financien.png\n| logo_width           = 250x250px\n| logo_caption         = Logo of the Ministry of Finance\n| image                = Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn wintertuin1.jpg\n| image_size           = 250x250px\n| image_caption        = Building of the Ministry of Finance\n| formed               = {{Start date and years ago|1798|03|12|df=y}} \n| jurisdiction         = [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]\n| headquarters         = Korte Voorhout 7, [[The Hague]], [[Netherlands]]\n| employees            = 1,500\n| budget               = \u20ac11,7 billion (2013)<ref>{{in lang|nl}} [http://rijksbegroting.minfin.nl/2013/voorbereiding/begroting?hoofdstuk=40.42 IX Financi\u00ebn en Nationale Schuld], Rijksoverheid, 18 September 2012</ref>\n| minister1_name       = [[Wopke Hoekstra]]\n| minister1_pfo        = [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands|Minister of Finance]]\n| minister2_name       = \n| minister2_pfo        = \n| deputyminister1_name = [[Hans Vijlbrief]] <br/> [[Alexandra van Huffelen]]\n| deputyminister1_pfo  = [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands#List of State Secretaries for Finance|State Secretaries for Finance]] \n| chief1_name          = Manon Leijten\n| chief1_position      = Secretary-General\n| deputy               = \n| website              = [https://www.government.nl/ministries/ministry-of-finance Ministry of Finance]\n}}\n\nThe '''Ministry of Finance''' ({{lang-nl|Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn}}; FIN) is the [[Ministries of the Netherlands|Dutch Ministry]] responsible for [[Economic policy]], [[Monetary policy]], [[Fiscal policy]], [[Tax policy]], [[Incomes policy]], [[Regulation|Regulations]], [[Government budget]] and the [[Financial market]]. The Ministry was created in 1798 as the Department of Finance of the Batavian Republic. In 1876, it became the Ministry of Finance. The [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands|Minister of Finance]] ({{lang-nl|Minister van Financi\u00ebn}}) is the head of the Ministry and a member of the [[Cabinet of the Netherlands]]. The current Minister is [[Wopke Hoekstra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2199353-wopke-hoekstra-cda-bezige-bij-en-nu-minister-van-financien.html|title=Wopke Hoekstra (CDA), bezige bij en nu minister van Financi\u00ebn|publisher=NOS|date=23 October 2017|accessdate=15 January 2018|language=nl}}</ref>\n\n{{Politics of the Netherlands}}\n\n==History==\nThe ministry was founded in 1798. In the early history of the ministry, the Prime Minister often served as Minister of Finance. [[Pieter Philip van Bosse]] served as Minister of Finance five times. Since 1965 a [[State Secretary (Netherlands)|State Secretary]] has been appointed each formation with responsibility for taxation. The most recent Prime Minister to serve as his own Minister of Finance was [[Jelle Zijlstra]] (1966\u201367).\n\n==Responsibilities==\nThe ministry has the duty to \"guard the treasury and aim for a financially sound and prosperous state of the Netherlands.\n* It is responsible for the income and expenditure of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]].\n* It collects the taxes and develops fiscal legislation.\n* It seeks to expend the budget of the government responsibly, efficiently and effectively.\n* It is also responsible for financial-economic policy.\n* It supervises the [[financial market]]s, [[bank]]s and financial transfers.\n\n==Organisation==\nThe ministry is currently headed by one minister and one [[Secretary of state|State secretary]]. The ministry's main office is located in the centre of [[The Hague]] at the Korte Voorhout. It employs almost 1,500 civil servants. The civil service is headed by a secretary general and a deputy secretary general, who head a system of four directorates general:\n* General Treasury (financial economic policy), lead by the [[Treasurer-General]]<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/generale-thesaurie |title = Generale Thesaurie |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Agency of the General Treasury\n** Directorate Financing\n** Directorate Financial Markets\n** Directorate Foreign Financial Relations\n* Directorate General for the Budget<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/directoraat-generaal-rijksbegroting |title = Directoraat-generaal Rijksbegroting |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Directorate Budget Affairs\n** Inspection of National Finances\n* Directorate General for Fiscal Affairs<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/directoraat-generaal-voor-fiscale-zaken |title = Directoraat-generaal voor Fiscale Zaken |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Directorate General Fiscal Policy\n** Directorate Taxation Management\n** Directorate International Affairs and Excise Tax\n* Directorate General for Taxation\n\nIt is also responsible for several decentralized services:\n* The agency in Amsterdam{{what|date=November 2019}}\n* The [[Tax and Customs Administration]], the Dutch revenue service, which includes the [[customs]] service and the [[fiscal policy]]\n* Service for State Property\n\nThe ministry also owns most of the shares the Dutch government owns, which are all nationalized companies. These include\n*[[ABN AMRO|ABN AMRO Group NV]] (100%)\n*[[Connexxion|Connexxion Holding NV]] (33%)\n*[[COVRA|Centrale Organisatie voor Radio-actief Afval (COVRA) NV]] (100%)\n*[[De Nederlandsche Bank|De Nederlandsche Bank NV]] (100%)\n*[[Koninklijke Nederlandse Munt|Koninklijke Nederlandse Munt NV]] (100%)\n*[[Gasunie|NV Nederlandse Gasunie]] (100%)\n*[[Nederlandse Spoorwegen|NV Nederlandse Spoorwegen]] (100%)\n*[[Netherlands Public Broadcasting|NOB Holding]] (100%)\n*[[Schiphol|NV Luchthaven Schiphol]] (75,8%)\n*[[Rotterdam|Havenbedrijf Rotterdam]] (33%)\n*[[Gasunie|Gasterra (previously: Gasunie T&S)]] (100%)\n*[[KLM|Koninklijke Luchtvaart Maatschappij]] NV (5,9%)\n*[[SNS Bank|SNS Bank NV]] (100%)\n*[[SNS REAAL|SNS REAAL NV]] (100%)\n*[[TenneT]] (100%)\n\nIt also responsible for overseeing the independent government [[financial regulation|financial regulatory]] agency:\n* [[Netherlands Authority for the Financial Markets]] (AFM)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|nl}} [http://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/fin Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn] <small>(Rijksoverheid)</small>\n\n{{Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands}}\n{{Government of the Netherlands}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)}}\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 1798]]\n[[Category:Finance ministries|Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Government ministries of the Netherlands|Finance]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 1798]]\n[[Category:1798 establishments in the Batavian Republic]]\n[[Category:Finance in the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name                 = Ministry of Finance\n| native_name          = {{lang-nl|Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn}}\n| type                 = Department\n| logo                 = Logo-ministerie-van-financien.png\n| logo_width           = 250x250px\n| logo_caption         = Logo of the Ministry of Finance\n| image                = Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn wintertuin1.jpg\n| image_size           = 250x250px\n| image_caption        = Building of the Ministry of Finance\n| formed               = {{Start date and years ago|1798|03|12|df=y}} \n| jurisdiction         = [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]]\n| headquarters         = Korte Voorhout 7, [[The Hague]], [[Netherlands]]\n| employees            = 1,500\n| budget               = \u20ac11,7 billion (2013)<ref>{{in lang|nl}} [http://rijksbegroting.minfin.nl/2013/voorbereiding/begroting?hoofdstuk=40.42 IX Financi\u00ebn en Nationale Schuld], Rijksoverheid, 18 September 2012</ref>\n| minister1_name       = [[Wopke Hoekstra]]\n| minister1_pfo        = [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands|Minister of Finance]]\n| minister2_name       = \n| minister2_pfo        = \n| deputyminister1_name = [[Hans Vijlbrief]] <br/> [[Alexandra van Huffelen]]\n| deputyminister1_pfo  = [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands#List of State Secretaries for Finance|State Secretaries for Finance]] \n| chief1_name          = Manon Leijten\n| chief1_position      = Secretary-General\n| deputy               = \n| website              = [https://www.government.nl/ministries/ministry-of-finance Ministry of Finance]\n}}\n\nThe '''Ministry of Finance''' ({{lang-nl|Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn}}; FIN) is the [[Ministries of the Netherlands|Dutch Ministry]] responsible for [[Economic policy]], [[Monetary policy]], [[Fiscal policy]], [[Tax policy]], [[Incomes policy]], [[Regulation|Regulations]], [[Government budget]] and the [[Financial market]]. The Ministry was created in 1798 as the Department of Finance of the Batavian Republic. In 1876, it became the Ministry of Finance. The [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands|Minister of Finance]] ({{lang-nl|Minister van Financi\u00ebn}}) is the head of the Ministry and a member of the [[Cabinet of the Netherlands]]. The current Minister is [[Wopke Hoekstra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2199353-wopke-hoekstra-cda-bezige-bij-en-nu-minister-van-financien.html|title=Wopke Hoekstra (CDA), bezige bij en nu minister van Financi\u00ebn|publisher=NOS|date=23 October 2017|accessdate=15 January 2018|language=nl}}</ref>\n\n{{Politics of the Netherlands}}\n\n==History==\nThe ministry was founded in 1798. In the early history of the ministry, the Prime Minister often served as Minister of Finance. [[Pieter Philip van Bosse]] served as Minister of Finance five times. Since 1965 a [[State Secretary (Netherlands)|State Secretary]] has been appointed each formation with responsibility for taxation. The most recent Prime Minister to serve as his own Minister of Finance was [[Jelle Zijlstra]] (1966\u201367).\n\n==Responsibilities==\nThe ministry has the duty to \"guard the treasury and aim for a financially sound and prosperous state of the Netherlands.\n* It is responsible for the income and expenditure of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]].\n* It collects the taxes and develops fiscal legislation.\n* It seeks to expend the budget of the government responsibly, efficiently and effectively.\n* It is also responsible for financial-economic policy.\n* It supervises the [[financial market]]s, [[bank]]s and financial transfers.\n\n==Organisation==\nThe ministry is currently headed by one minister and one [[Secretary of state|State secretary]]. The ministry's main office is located in the centre of [[The Hague]] at the Korte Voorhout. It employs almost 1,500 civil servants. The civil service is headed by a secretary general and a deputy secretary general, who head a system of four directorates general:\n* General Treasury (financial economic policy), lead by the [[Treasurer General]]<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/generale-thesaurie |title = Generale Thesaurie |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Agency of the General Treasury\n** Directorate Financing\n** Directorate Financial Markets\n** Directorate Foreign Financial Relations\n* Directorate General for the Budget<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/directoraat-generaal-rijksbegroting |title = Directoraat-generaal Rijksbegroting |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Directorate Budget Affairs\n** Inspection of National Finances\n* Directorate General for Fiscal Affairs<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/ministerie-van-financien/organisatie/organogram/directoraat-generaal-voor-fiscale-zaken |title = Directoraat-generaal voor Fiscale Zaken |language = Dutch |website = Rijksoverheid |access-date = 1 April 2020 }}</ref>\n** Directorate General Fiscal Policy\n** Directorate Taxation Management\n** Directorate International Affairs and Excise Tax\n* Directorate General for Taxation\n\nIt is also responsible for several decentralized services:\n* The agency in Amsterdam{{what|date=November 2019}}\n* The [[Tax and Customs Administration]], the Dutch revenue service, which includes the [[customs]] service and the [[fiscal policy]]\n* Service for State Property\n\nThe ministry also owns most of the shares the Dutch government owns, which are all nationalized companies. These include\n*[[ABN AMRO|ABN AMRO Group NV]] (100%)\n*[[Connexxion|Connexxion Holding NV]] (33%)\n*[[COVRA|Centrale Organisatie voor Radio-actief Afval (COVRA) NV]] (100%)\n*[[De Nederlandsche Bank|De Nederlandsche Bank NV]] (100%)\n*[[Koninklijke Nederlandse Munt|Koninklijke Nederlandse Munt NV]] (100%)\n*[[Gasunie|NV Nederlandse Gasunie]] (100%)\n*[[Nederlandse Spoorwegen|NV Nederlandse Spoorwegen]] (100%)\n*[[Netherlands Public Broadcasting|NOB Holding]] (100%)\n*[[Schiphol|NV Luchthaven Schiphol]] (75,8%)\n*[[Rotterdam|Havenbedrijf Rotterdam]] (33%)\n*[[Gasunie|Gasterra (previously: Gasunie T&S)]] (100%)\n*[[KLM|Koninklijke Luchtvaart Maatschappij]] NV (5,9%)\n*[[SNS Bank|SNS Bank NV]] (100%)\n*[[SNS REAAL|SNS REAAL NV]] (100%)\n*[[TenneT]] (100%)\n\nIt also responsible for overseeing the independent government [[financial regulation|financial regulatory]] agency:\n* [[Netherlands Authority for the Financial Markets]] (AFM)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|nl}} [http://www.rijksoverheid.nl/ministeries/fin Ministerie van Financi\u00ebn] <small>(Rijksoverheid)</small>\n\n{{Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands}}\n{{Government of the Netherlands}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)}}\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 1798]]\n[[Category:Finance ministries|Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Government ministries of the Netherlands|Finance]]\n[[Category:Ministries established in 1798]]\n[[Category:1798 establishments in the Batavian Republic]]\n[[Category:Finance in the Netherlands]]\n", "name_user": "Tristan Surtel", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOrganisation:hyphen", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Finance_(Netherlands)"}
{"title_page": "Despicable Me (franchise)", "text_new": "{{short description|Animated film franchise}}\n{{Italic title}}{{Infobox media franchise\n| title = ''Despicable Me''\n| image = Despicable Me logo 2.svg\n| imagesize = 200px\n| creator = [[Sergio Pablos]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thespastudios.com/despicable-me.html |title=Despicable Me |publisher=The SPA Studios |date= |accessdate=August 20, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121206063710/http://www.thespastudios.com/despicable-me.html|archive-date=December 6, 2012}}</ref>\n| owner = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Illumination (company)|Illumination]]\n* [[Universal Pictures]]\n}}\n| films = \n* {{nowrap|''[[Despicable Me]]''}} (2010)\n* {{nowrap|''[[Despicable Me 2]]''}} (2013)\n* {{nowrap|''[[Despicable Me 3]]''}} (2017)\n* {{nowrap|''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''}} (2015)\n* {{nowrap|''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''}} (2020)\n\n| shorts   = [[#Short films|See below]]\n| vgs    = \n* [[Despicable Me (franchise)#Despicable Me: The Game|Despicable Me: The Game]]\n* {{nowrap|''[[Despicable Me: Minion Rush]]''}}\n* {{nowrap|''[[Minions Paradise]]''}}\n| attractions = [[Despicable Me Minion Mayhem]] (2012\u2013present)\n}} \n'''''Despicable Me''''' is an [[animation|animated]] [[media franchise]] produced by [[Illumination (company)|Illumination]] and distributed by [[Universal Pictures]], consisting of four feature films, thirteen short films, and additional merchandise. It centers on Gru, a reformed super-villain (who later becomes a father and secret agent), his yellow-colored [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]]; his three adopted daughters, Margo, Edith and Agnes, Dr. Nefario, and his wife, Lucy Wilde.\n\nThe franchise began with the 2010 film [[Despicable Me|of the same name]] and its 2013 and 2017 sequels ''[[Despicable Me 2]]'' (2013) and ''[[Despicable Me 3]]'' (2017). A prequel featuring Gru's Minions, titled ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'', was released in 2015. A sequel to ''Minions'' titled ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]'' will be released in 2020.\n\nIt also includes a ride attraction, ''[[Despicable Me Minion Mayhem]]'', at [[Universal Studios Florida]], [[Universal Studios Hollywood]], and [[Universal Studios Japan]]. It is the [[List of highest-grossing animated films#Highest-grossing animated franchises and film series|highest-grossing animated film franchise]] in box office history, and the 15th highest-grossing film franchise of all time. The film series has grossed $3.7 billion to-date.\n\n==Film series==\n===Main series===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Film\n! scope=\"col\" | Release date\n! scope=\"col\" | Director\n! scope=\"col\" | Screenplay by\n! scope=\"col\" | Story by\n! scope=\"col\" | Producer(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Status\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" | ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | {{Start date|2010|7|09}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|  [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]] and [[Pierre Coffin]]\n| [[Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio]]\n| [[Sergio Pablos]]\n| Chris Meledandri, John Cohen and [[Janet Healy]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Released\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" | ''[[Despicable Me 2]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | {{Start date|2013|7|3}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"| [[Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Chris Meledandri and Janet Healy\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" | ''[[Despicable Me 3]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | {{Start date|2017|6|30}}\n| Pierre Coffin, [[Kyle Balda]] and Eric Guillon\n|}\n\n====''Despicable Me'' (2010)====\n{{main|Despicable Me}}\n''Despicable Me'', the first film in the series, and the first film from [[Illumination (company)|Illumination]], was released on July 9, 2010. It was directed by [[Pierre Coffin]] and [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]], based on an original story by [[Sergio Pablos]] and written by [[Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio]]. The film stars [[Steve Carell]] as the voice of Felonious Gru, [[Miranda Cosgrove]] as Margo, [[Dana Gaier]] as Edith, [[Elsie Fisher]] as Agnes, [[Jason Segel]] as Vector, [[Russell Brand]] as Dr. Nefario and [[Julie Andrews]] as Marlena Gru, Gru's mother. It tells the story of Gru, a super-villain who adopts three girls, Margo, Edith and Agnes, from an orphanage to try and steal a shrink ray from Vector (otherwise known as Victor), his rival, to shrink and steal Earth's moon. ''Despicable Me'' received positive reviews, and grossed over $543 million worldwide, against a budget of $69 million, launching a new franchise.\n\n====''Despicable Me 2'' (2013)====\n{{main|Despicable Me 2}}\nA sequel, ''Despicable Me 2'', released on July 3, 2013, was once again directed by [[Pierre Coffin]] and [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]], and written by [[Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio]]. [[Steve Carell]], [[Russell Brand]], [[Miranda Cosgrove]], [[Dana Gaier]],<ref name=\"behindthethrills\">{{cite news|title=Despicable Me Minion Mayhem is now open at Universal Studios|url=http://behindthethrills.com/2012/07/despicable-me-minion-mayhem-is-now-open-at-universal-studios/|accessdate=August 20, 2012|newspaper=Behind the Thrills|date=July 2, 2012|author=Racheal}}</ref> and [[Elsie Fisher]]<ref name=\"behindthethrills\" /> reprise their roles as Felonious Gru, Dr. Nefario, Margo, Edith and Agnes respectively.<ref name=\"THRDM2\">{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Borys|title=Steve Coogan Joining Voice Cast for 'Despicable Me 2' (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/steve-coogan-despicable-me-sequel-318736|accessdate=October 15, 2012|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 1, 2012}}</ref> [[Kristen Wiig]], who voiced Miss Hattie in the first film, voices Lucy Wilde, an agent of the Anti-Villain League who recruits Gru to take down a new villain. New cast members include [[Benjamin Bratt]] as Eduardo;<ref>{{cite web|title=Al Pacino Departs Despicable Me 2|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=103761|work=[[ComingSoon.net]]|publisher=[[CraveOnline]]|date=May 3, 2013|accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> Bratt replaced the previously cast [[Al Pacino]].<ref name=\"DDM2Pacino\">{{cite news|last=Fleming|first=Mike|title=Al Pacino Makes Animated Film Debut In \u2018Despicable Me 2\u2032|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/02/al-pacino-signs-on-for-despicable-me-2/|accessdate=October 15, 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=February 3, 2012}}</ref> [[Steve Coogan]] voices Silas Ramsbottom, lead director of the Anti-Villain League (AVL).<ref name=THRDM2 /> The sequel was met with generally positive reviews and grossed more than its predecessor with over $970 million worldwide.<ref name=RTDM2 /><ref name=BOMDM2 />\n\n====''Despicable Me 3'' (2017)====\n{{main|Despicable Me 3}}\nA third film, ''Despicable Me 3'', was released on June 30, 2017. The film was directed by [[Pierre Coffin]] and [[Kyle Balda]], and co-directed by Eric Guillon.<ref>{{cite news|title=Benedict Cumberbatch to Voice The Grinch, Trey Parker the Despicable Me 3 Villain|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/676327-benedict-cumberbatch-to-voice-the-grinch-trey-parker-the-despicable-me-3-villain|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|accessdate=December 14, 2016|date=April 13, 2016 }}</ref> [[Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio]], the writers of the first two films, returned to write the screenplay for the third film.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u2018Despicable Me\u2019 Screenwriter Discusses Local Honor, Theme Park Attraction|url=http://conejovalley.happeningmag.com/despicable-me-screenwriter-discusses-local-honor-theme-park-attraction/|publisher=Conejo Valley Happening|accessdate=July 24, 2015|quote=We just started writing Despicable Me 3,...|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150724220041/http://conejovalley.happeningmag.com/despicable-me-screenwriter-discusses-local-honor-theme-park-attraction/|archive-date=July 24, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Steve Carell]], [[Kristen Wiig]], [[Miranda Cosgrove]], [[Dana Gaier]], and [[Steve Coogan]] reprise their roles as Felonious, Gru, Lucy Wilde, Margo, Edith, and Silas Ramsbottom respectively (with [[Julie Andrews]] reprising her role as Marlena Gru, and [[Pierre Coffin]] as the Minions). Carell also voiced Gru's long-lost twin brother Dru.<ref>{{cite web|last=Franich|first=Darren|url= http://www.ew.com/article/2016/04/13/trey-parker-despicable-me-3-villain|title=Trey Parker Will Voice The Villain In ''Despicable Me 3''|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Nequinto|first=Denise|title='Despicable Me 3' 2017 Plot: Gru Experiences Sibling Rivalry, Faces New Villain|url=http://www.citizenoracle.com/2016/09/30/despicable-me-3-2017-plot-gru-experiences-sibling-rivalry-faces-new-villain/|accessdate=December 12, 2016|work=CitizenOracle|date=September 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010125828/http://www.citizenoracle.com/2016/09/30/despicable-me-3-2017-plot-gru-experiences-sibling-rivalry-faces-new-villain/|archive-date=October 10, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> New cast members included [[Trey Parker]] as the voice of Balthazar Bratt, and Nev Scharrel (replacing [[Elsie Fisher]], due to being mature for the role) as the new voice of Agnes.<ref name=\"slashfilm\">{{cite web |last= Anderton |first= Ethan |url= http://www.slashfilm.com/despicable-me-3-trailer/ |title= 'Despicable Me 3' Trailer: 'South Park's Trey Parker Plays Gru's Latest Nemesis |work= [[/Film]] |date= December 14, 2016 |accessdate= December 14, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"CSCastAndTrailer\">{{cite web |last= Lesnick |first=Silas |url= http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/trailers/792971-despicable-me-3-trailer#/slide/1 |title= Gru is Back in the Despicable Me 3 Trailer! |work= ComingSoon.net |date= December 14, 2016 |accessdate= December 14, 2016}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews by critics and grossed more than its predecessors with over $1 billion worldwide.\n\n====''Despicable Me 4''====<!-- Do not add \"(TBA)\" since there has not been an official announcement on the release for a possible fourth Despicable Me film -->\nIllumination's CEO [[Chris Meledandri]] revealed in an interview in September 2017 that a fourth ''Despicable Me'' film is in the works.<ref>{{cite web |last= Sakoui |first= Anousha |last2= Palmeri |first2= Christopher |title= In Dismal Summer, 'Despicable Me 3' Producer Delivers $1 Billion |url= https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-12/in-dismal-summer-despicable-me-3-producer-delivers-1-billion |publisher= Bloomberg |accessdate= September 28, 2017 |date= September 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\n===Prequel series===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Film\n! scope=\"col\" | Release date\n! scope=\"col\" | Director\n! scope=\"col\" | Written by\n! scope=\"col\" | Producer(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Status\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" | ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | {{Start date|2015|7|10}}\n| Pierre Coffin and Kyle Balda\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Brian Lynch (writer)|Brian Lynch]]\n| Chris Meledandri and Janet Healy\n| Released\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" | ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center\" | {{Start date|TBA}}\n| Kyle Balda, Brad Ableson and Jonathan del Val\n| Chris Meledandri, Janet Healy and Chris Renaud\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n====''Minions'' (2015)====\n[[File:Minions (film) yellow logo.svg|thumb|right|220px|Logo of the first ''Minions'' film]]\n{{main|Minions (film)}}\nA prequel to ''Despicable Me'', featuring the [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]], was released on July 10, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Universal Dates Minions Movie Dec. 19, 2014|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/08/untitled-minions-movied-slated-for-december-19-2014/|accessdate=August 22, 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=August 21, 2012}}</ref> Written by [[Brian Lynch (writer)|Brian Lynch]], it was directed by [[Pierre Coffin]] and [[Kyle Balda]] and produced by Chris Meledandri and Janet Healy.<ref>{{cite news|last=Fleming|first=Mike|title=Illumination And Universal Hatch \u2018Despicable Me\u2019 Spinoff About The Minions|url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/07/despicable-me-spinoff-minions-illumination-entertainment-universal/|accessdate=July 24, 2012|newspaper=Deadline|date=July 23, 2012}}</ref> [[Sandra Bullock]] voiced Scarlet Overkill, the villain of the film<ref name=\"DeadlineBullock\">{{cite news|last=Fleming|first=Mike|title=Sandra Bullock To Voice Super-Villain In \u2018Minions\u2019 Spinoff For Illumination/Universal|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/02/sandra-bullock-to-voice-super-villain-in-minions-spinoff-for-illuminationuniversal/|accessdate=February 14, 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=February 11, 2013}}</ref> and [[Jon Hamm]] voiced her husband and inventor, Herb Overkill.<ref name=\"DeadlineHamm\">{{cite news|last=Fleming|first=Mike|title=At Illumination, Jon Hamm Lends Voice To \u2018Minions\u2019 Movie; Tito Ortiz Returns As Executive|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/04/at-illumination-jon-hamm-lends-voice-to-minions-movie-tito-ortiz-returns-as-executive/|accessdate=May 1, 2013|newspaper=Deadline|date=April 30, 2013}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews by critics and grossed more than $1.1 billion worldwide.\n\n====''Minions: The Rise of Gru'' (2020)====\n{{Main|Minions: The Rise of Gru}}\nA sequel to ''Minions'' titled ''Minions: The Rise of Gru'' was officially announced on January 25, 2017, with a original scheduled release date of July 3, 2020, but was delayed due to the [[2019-2020 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"VarietySing2Set2020\">{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=\u2018Sing 2\u2019 Set for Christmas Day 2020 Release|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/sing-movie-sequel-christmas-2020-secret-life-of-pets-2-minions-2-1201970096/|accessdate=January 26, 2017|work=Variety|date=January 25, 2017}}</ref> It will be directed by [[Kyle Balda]] and Brad Ableson.<ref name=Minions2Crew>{{cite web|last1=Ableson|first1=Brad|title=Excited to share some news: I\u2019m co-directing Minions 2! Proud 2 be working with @IllumEnt director Kyle Balda & writer @BrianLynch #minions2pic.twitter.com/MS5iylsFEJ|url=https://twitter.com/BradAbleson/status/887750241528590336|website=@BradAbleson|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=19 July 2017|date=19 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Short films==\nA total of 13 short films have been released in the franchise. Three short films based on ''Despicable Me'' (2010) were released on December 2010 on the film's DVD and Blu-ray.<ref>{{cite news | first=Juan | last=Calonge | url=http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=5185 | title=Despicable Me Blu-ray and 3D BD Announced | publisher=blu-ray.com | date=September 22, 2010 | accessdate=November 22, 2010}}</ref> The ''Despicable Me 2'' DVD and Blu-ray, released on December 2013, included another three short films.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hannett|first=Michelle|title=DESPICABLE ME 2 Coming To Blu-ray/DVD December 10; Available On Digital HD November 26|url=http://www.wearemoviegeeks.com/2013/10/despicable-me-2-coming-to-blu-raydvd-december-10-available-on-digital-hd-november-26/|accessdate=September 7, 2017|publisher=wearemoviegeeks.com|date=October 7, 2013}}</ref> Three short films were released in 2015 on the Blu-ray and DVD of ''Minions,'' while one short film was released in the Blu-ray and DVD of ''Despicable Me 3'' (2017).<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw|first=Lucas|title=France Can Now Offer Film Productions 150 % More Money|url=http://www.thewrap.com/movies/article/france-can-now-offer-film-productions-150-percent-more-money-101401|accessdate=August 20, 2013|newspaper=The Wrap|date=July 5, 2013|quote=The animated short \u201cMinions series,\u201d which will screen next year with a spin-off of \"Despicable Me,\" just qualified for a rebate, as did Eleanor Coppola's \"Bonjour Anne.\"}}</ref>\n\nA short film titled ''Mower Minions'', was released in 2016 with ''[[The Secret Life of Pets]]'', being the first short Minions film released theatrically.<ref name=\"PRMowerMinions\">{{cite press release|author1=Universal Pictures|title=Illumination Entertainment And Universal Pictures Announce Mower Minions, An All-New Short Film Starring The Minions, Will Debut In Theaters With The Secret Life Of Pets|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/illumination-entertainment-and-universal-pictures-announce-mower-minions-an-all-new-short-film-starring-the-minions-will-debut-in-theaters-with-the-secret-life-of-pets-300251385.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=June 18, 2016|date=April 13, 2016}}</ref> A second theatrical short film was released in 2018 with ''[[The Grinch (film)|The Grinch]]'' (2018), while another one was released in ''The Grinch'''s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\n==={{anchor|Home Makeover}} ''Home Makeover'' (2010)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me'' (2010)'s DVD and Blu-ray. Grouped in DVD ''Minion Madness'' (2010).\n\nAfter the events of ''Despicable Me'', two Minions help Margo, Edith and Agnes renovate Gru's house, so the inspector does not take the girls back to Miss Hattie's Home for Girls.\n\n==={{anchor|Orientation Day}} ''Orientation Day'' (2010)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me'' (2010)'s DVD and Blu-ray. Grouped in DVD ''Minion Madness'' (2010).\n\nThree new Minions go for bomb-carrying duty, which was harder than they thought when they suddenly have an argument with two others carrying a giant bomb.\n\n==={{anchor|Banana}} ''Banana'' (2010)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me'' (2010)'s DVD and Blu-ray. Grouped in DVD ''Minion Madness'' (2010).\n\nThree minions fight over a banana. In the process, they wreak havoc in the Minions' workplace.\n\n==={{anchor|Puppy}} ''Puppy'' (2013)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me 2'' (2013)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nA minion watches neighbors walking their dogs on the street, which leads him to search for a puppy of his own. After several failed attempts, he comes across a [[UFO]] that takes the role of a puppy for him. After many happy moments, the UFO along with its master is expelled for the mess the UFO has made in Gru's home. After the minion finds out that his pet is homesick, he sends an email to the UFO's home planet and allows it to return home.\n\n==={{anchor|Panic in the Mailroom}} ''Panic in the Mailroom'' (2013)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me 2'' (2013)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nTwo Minions, Ken and Mike, are working in a package room to send parcels through different parts of the lab, while Ken is busy playing a handheld video game. When a package containing expired PX-41 (the serum that El Macho used to transform the Minions and himself in ''Despicable Me 2''), gets jammed in the pneumatic delivery system, it transforms Mike into an evil Minion but he keeps shifting back and forth between being transformed and back to his normal self, much to Ken's amusement. At the end, Mike spits out the PX-41 and it lands on some kittens, turning them evil.\n\n==={{anchor|Training Wheels}} ''Training Wheels'' (2013)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me 2'' (2013)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nAgnes is unsatisfied with her toy bike after collapsing off it while attempting to catch up to an ice cream truck with Margo, Edith and their friends. Three Minions then volunteer to modify the bike and help Agnes improve her skills.\n\n==={{anchor|Binky Nelson Unpacified}} ''Binky Nelson Unpacified'' (2015)===\nReleased in ''Minions'' (2015)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nAfter a successful robbery at a museum, the Nelsons tell their youngest son Binky, having lost his pacifier in the theft, that now he is a big boy and has to leave his pacifier. Binky at night sneaks into the museum and finds his pacifier. Just as he takes it the guard comes and finds all the museum artifacts missing and finds Binky and tells him to return all the property but instead he causes a statue to fall over the guard and takes his pacifier. In the end the Nelson parents return to see Binky at night in his room and find him sleeping calmly. As they leave the room Binky takes out the pacifier and the guard's hat and wears it.\n\n==={{anchor|Competition}} ''Competition'' (2015)===\nReleased in ''Minions'' (2015)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nUnder the same street the Minions hitchhiked in ''Minions'', two Minions challenge themselves to numerous attacks, ending up on the lab's conveyor belt in the process.\n\n==={{anchor|Cro Minion}} ''Cro Minion'' (2015)===\nReleased in ''Minions'' (2015)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nTwo Minions look after a cave baby while a caveman goes to find a bull to eat for lunch. But it is harder than the Minions think.\n\n==={{anchor|Mower Minions}} ''Mower Minions'' (2016)===\nReleased theatrically with ''[[The Secret Life of Pets]]'' (2016).<ref name=PRMowerMinions />\n\nIn this short, five Minions mow a lawn at the local old people's home to try and earn allowances to buy a blender they have seen on a TV commercial. However, all their work results were chaotic, and four of them were in terrible states after the chaos, such as one Minion having their head stuck in a bee hive, another Minion blackened and naked after an explosion, another being shaped like a balloon in the hazmat, and another Minion ends up nauseous with their face turning green. But as it turns out, the old people were very entertained. For this the Minions get 2000 pennies and are able to purchase the blender. However they then see a commercial of an improved version of the blender and then go to earn more money to buy that one.\n\n==={{anchor|The Secret Life of Kyle}} ''The Secret Life of Kyle'' (2017)===\nReleased in ''Despicable Me 3'' (2017)'s DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nAfter the events of ''Despicable Me 3'', we follow Kyle and his secret life when Gru and his family are gone. This short was directed by Bruno Chauffard and Glenn McCoy.\n\n==={{anchor|Yellow is the New Black}} ''Yellow is the New Black'' (2018)===\nReleased theatrically with ''[[The Grinch (film)|The Grinch]]'' (2018).<ref name=\"PRMowerMinions\" />\n\nBefore they all make their big escape from prison in ''Despicable Me 3'', a couple of lucky Minions get a taste of freedom as they break free with the help of one of their fellow human inmates.\n\n==={{anchor|Santa's Little Helpers}} ''Santa's Little Helpers'' (2019)===\nReleased in ''The Grinch's'' DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nKevin, Stuart and Bob, having been accidentally dropped off at the North Pole, make the most of the situation by trying to become elves.\n\n==={{anchor|Minion Scouts}} ''Minion Scouts'' (2019)===\nReleased in ''[[The Secret Life of Pets 2]]'' (2019) DVD and Blu-ray.\n\nAfter being dazzled by the girls, a group of Minions become scouts in an attempt to earn badges.\n\n==Video games==\n===''Despicable Me: The Game''===\n''Despicable Me: The Game'' is an adventure/action game released with the first film, on [[PlayStation 2]], [[Wii]], and [[PlayStation Portable]] systems.<ref name=BWDMTheGame /> During the game, the player controls Gru as he fights off enemies. ''Despicable Me: The Game \u2013 Minion Mayhem'', on the other hand, is released on [[Nintendo DS]] systems only.<ref name=BWDMTheGame>{{cite press release|author1=D3Publisher|title=D3Publisher Launches Despicable Me TM: The GameTM for Wii\u2122, Nintendo DS\u2122, PlayStation\u00ae2 System and PSP\u00ae System|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20100706005181/en/D3Publisher-Launches-Despicable-TM-GameTM-Wii%E2%84%A2-Nintendo|publisher=Business Wire|accessdate=November 1, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101130512/http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20100706005181/en/D3Publisher-Launches-Despicable-TM-GameTM-Wii%E2%84%A2-Nintendo#.VFTagJzF_1E|archivedate=November 1, 2014|date=July 6, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> Instead of controlling Gru himself, the player controls his Minions.\n\n===''Despicable Me: Minion Rush''===\n{{main|Despicable Me: Minion Rush}}\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Minion Rush.png|thumb|150px|Despicable Me: Minion Rush app icon]] -->\nAn action video game (developed by [[Gameloft]]), titled ''Despicable Me: Minion Rush'', also played as a Minion who must defeat Vector, El Macho and two villains made for the game, was released with the second film, on [[iPhone]], [[iPad]], [[Windows Phone]], [[Windows 8]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[Tizen]] and [[Blackberry 10]] devices.<ref>{{cite news|last=O'Connel|first=Sean|title='Despicable Me' Game: Our Exclusive First Look at 'Minion Rush'|url=http://www.fandango.com/movieblog/despicable-me-game-our-exclusive-first-look-at-minion-rush-738612.html|accessdate=June 3, 2013|newspaper=Fandango|date=May 30, 2013}}</ref><ref name=PRNewswireRush>{{cite news|title=Gameloft, Universal Pictures and Illumination Entertainment Launch \"Despicable Me: Minion Rush\"|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/gameloft-universal-pictures-and-illumination-entertainment-launch-despicable-me-minion-rush-211408991.html|accessdate=July 4, 2013|newspaper=PR Newswire|date=June 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Adam|first1=Zeis|title=Despicable Me: Minion Rush lands on BlackBerry 10|url=http://crackberry.com/despicable-me-minion-rush-lands-blackberry-10|publisher=CrackBerry.com|accessdate=July 14, 2015|date=October 16, 2013}}</ref> As of October 2016, the game had been downloaded more than 750 million times.<ref>{{cite press release|author1=Universal Pictures Home Entertainment|title=From Illumination Entertainment and Universal Pictures: The Secret Life of Pets|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/from-illumination-entertainment-and-universal-pictures-the-secret-life-of-pets-300338777.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=October 5, 2016|date=October 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===''Minions Paradise''===\n{{main|Minions Paradise}}\nA free-to-play mobile game developed by [[Electronic Arts]] (otherwise known as EA), titled ''Minions Paradise'', was released in summer 2015.<ref name=VarietyEAPact /> Playing as Phil, players will help Minions design and build their own utopia set in a tropical environment.<ref name=VarietyEAPact>{{cite news|last1=Morris|first1=Chris|title=\u2018Minions Paradise,\u2019 Other Mobile Games Set Under EA Pact with Illumination and Universal|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/minions-paradise-mobile-game-ea-illumination-despicable-me-1201467365/|accessdate=April 11, 2015|work=Variety|date=April 7, 2015}}</ref>\n==Books==\nNovels written by Annie Auerbach are based on the films.<ref name=\"audiofilemagazine\">{{cite web | url=http://www.audiofilemagazine.com/dbsearch/showreview.cfm?NUM=55549 | title=AudioFile audiobook review: DESPICABLE ME By Annie Auerbach, Read by Tim Curry | work=[[AudioFile (magazine)|AudioFile]] | accessdate=September 12, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"dogobooks\">{{cite web | url=http://www.dogobooks.com/despicable-me-the-junior-novel/book-review/0316083801 | title=Book Reviews - Despicable Me: The Junior Novel by Annie Auerbach | work=DogoBooks | accessdate=September 12, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"goodreads\">{{cite web | url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16173190-despicable-me-2 | title=Despicable Me 2: The Junior Novel by Annie Auerbach | work=[[Goodreads]] | accessdate=September 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Theme park attractions==\n{{main|Despicable Me Minion Mayhem}}\n''[[Despicable Me Minion Mayhem]]'' is a [[simulator ride]] that opened on July 2, 2012 at [[Universal Studios Florida]] and on April 12, 2014 at [[Universal Studios Hollywood]], starring [[Steve Carell]] as Gru, [[Miranda Cosgrove]] as Margo, [[Dana Gaier]] as Edith, [[Elsie Fisher]] as Agnes, and [[Pierre Coffin]] as the [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]]. A similar attraction (featuring a Japanese voice cast) opened on April 21, 2017 at [[Universal Studios Japan]].\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Main characters===\n* Felonious Gru<ref name=\"cinemablend\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Full-Minions-Trailer-Really-Goofy-71458.html|title=The Full Minions Trailer Is Really Goofy|last1=Baxter|first1=Joseph|date=May 14, 2015|work=cinemablend.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=November 23, 2016|quote=[\u2026] well before the days of their tenure with Felonious Gru [\u2026]}}</ref> or Felonius Gru<ref name=\"usatoday\">{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/04/10/minion-mayhem-mania-universal/7128937/|title=At Universal, the Minions 'have become our Mickey Mouse'|last1=Alexander|first1=Bryan|date=April 12, 2014|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=November 22, 2016|url-status=live|quote=[\u2026] into the ''Despicable Me'' world of supervillain Felonius Gru [\u2026]}}</ref> (voiced by [[Steve Carell]]): The grouchy but usually smart [[protagonist]] in the ''Despicable Me'' series who speaks with a Russian accent. He is the adoptive father of Margo, Edith, and Agnes, husband of Lucy, and the boss of the Minions. At the beginning of the [[Despicable Me|original film]], Gru is an ambitious supervillain, and seeks approval from his mother, until the adoption of the trio convinces him that their happiness is important. In the [[Despicable Me 2|second film]], Gru leaves his villainous past behind to care for the girls, but then soon joins forces - unwillingly - with secret agent Lucy Wilde, whom he later marries. In the [[Despicable Me 3|third film]], after he and Lucy are fired from their jobs at the Anti-Villain League, Gru learns that he has a twin brother, Dru. Along with Lucy and the girls, Gru meets Dru at his mansion in Freedonia, and they form a brotherly relationship over the course of the film. Felonious Gru was originally conceived as a [[Count Dracula|Dracula]]-like character, but directors Chris Renaud and Pierre Coffin later opted for a villain who would echo \"the world of [[James Bond]], thinking of characters like [[Auric Goldfinger|Goldfinger]] and obviously the Bond-ian world of technology\".<ref>[http://www.cartoonbrew.com/award-season-focus/directors-chris-renaud-and-pierre-coffin-on-creative-choices-and-challenges-in-despicable-me-films-93702.html Directors Chris Renaud and Pierre Coffin on Creative Choices and Challenges in \u201cDespicable Me\u201d Films], cartoonbrew.com, 1 October 2014, C. Edwards.</ref> Gru also bears some similarities with British comic-book character [[Grimly Feendish]], and with the pre-[[Crisis on Infinite Earths|Crisis]] version of [[Lex Luthor]].<ref name=\"empire\">[http://www.empireonline.com/movies/despicable/review/ Despicable Me Review], ''Empire'', 1 October 2010, Kim Newman</ref>\n* [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]] (voiced by [[Pierre Coffin]] in all films and the theme park attraction, [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]] in the first two films [except spin-offs and attractions], [[James Arnold Taylor]] in the 2010 video game, and [[Jemaine Clement]] as Jerry the Minion in the first film): Gru's small, yellow, comical henchmen who have one or two eyes. The Minions speak a language that Coffin created by mixing gibberish with words from many languages, including French, English, Spanish and Italian.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2013/despicable_me_2/notes.pdf|title=DESPICABLE ME 2 Production Notes|last=|first=|date=2013|website=visualhollywood.com|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304204926if_/http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2013/despicable_me_2/notes.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|access-date=2014-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/behind-screen/despicable-me-2-minions-5-579907|title='Despicable Me 2' Minions: 5 Things to Know|last=Giardina|first=Carolyn|date=July 4, 2013|website=|publisher=[[Hollywood Reporter]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=August 20, 2014}}</ref> Although seemingly nonsensical, the English-sounding words are dubbed for every country, in order to make them recognizable.<ref name=\"VarietyMinionsCameToLife\">{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/spotlight/chris-meledandri-honored-at-annecy-animation-festival-1201515021/|title=Chris Meledandri on How the \u2018Minions\u2019 Came to Life|date=June 11, 2015|work=Variety|last1=Debruge|first1=Peter|accessdate=October 30, 2015}}</ref> It is shown in ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'' that they have existed since the beginning of life on Earth, and desire above all else to serve the most terrible of villains.<ref name=\"CSMinionsSynopsis\">{{cite news|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=105595|title=Exclusive: The Synopsis for Minions|date=June 18, 2013|newspaper=ComingSoon.net|accessdate=June 18, 2013}}</ref> In the short film \"[[Despicable Me (franchise)#Banana (2010)|Banana]]\", the Minions are revealed to have an uncontrollable craving for fruits, especially [[bananas]]. Mentioned in the films and other media are Stuart, Kevin, Bob, Mel, Dave, Jerry, Carl, Tom,<ref name=\"HPTCDM2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.mcdhappymealtoys.com/2013/05/despicable-me-2.html|title=Desicable Me 2|date=June 19, 2013|newspaper=Happy Meal Toys Collection|accessdate=August 20, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813060440/http://www.mcdhappymealtoys.com/2013/05/despicable-me-2.html|archivedate=August 13, 2013}}</ref> Phil,<ref name=\"FFCharPosters\">{{cite news|url=http://www.filmofilia.com/despicable-me-2-minions-posters-161449/|title=Meet The Minions: DESPICABLE ME 2 Character Posters With Phil, Carl, Tim, Kevin & Stuart|last=Standal|first=Jeanne|date=June 28, 2013|newspaper=FilmoFilia|accessdate=August 20, 2013}}</ref> Tim,<ref name=\"FFCharPosters\" /> and Jorge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.universalorlando.com/Merchandise/Gift/Despicable-Me-Minion-Jorge-Plush.html|title=Despicable Me Minion Jorge Plush|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[Universal Orlando]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=August 20, 2013}}</ref>\n* The Girls: Three sisters, whom Gru adopts to further his scheme in the first film and gradually comes to love.\n** Margo (voiced by [[Miranda Cosgrove]]): The mature oldest sister. In the first film, among the trio, Margo was the most suspicious of Gru initially; but came to trust him at the end of the film. She is something of a protectress to her sisters.\n** Edith (voiced by [[Dana Gaier]]): The [[tomboy]]ish middle sister; the first to enjoy Gru's eclectic possessions, when adopted by him. Practices [[martial arts]] in the second film.\n** Agnes (voiced by [[Elsie Fisher]] in the first two films; Nev Scharrel in the third film): The happy-go-lucky youngest sister, and the quickest to trust Gru in the first film. She is presented as an innocent, against her more worldly sisters, and has a strong love for unicorns. In the third film, she \"adopts\" a one-horned goat whom she names Lucky after mistaking him for a unicorn. Even after learning he was a goat, Agnes continues to love Lucky.\n* Lucy Wilde (voiced by [[Kristen Wiig]]): A cunning secret agent who has teamed up with Gru to hunt down an extremely dangerous super-villain. She loves one-upping Gru with her quirky gadgets and has perfected her own form of martial arts by combining [[jujitsu]], [[krav maga]], [[Aztec warfare]] and [[krumping]]. After 147 dates, she marries Gru and becomes the girls' mother.\n* Dr. Nefario (voiced by [[Russell Brand]], JB Blanc in the video game): Gru's hearing-impaired inventor and partner-in-crime who speaks with a British accent. He seems to have a romantic interest in Gru's mother, Marlena. He is planned to join Gru, Lucy and the Girls to meet Dru in the third film, but absent from the film having accidentally frozen himself in carbonite, similar to that of [[Han Solo]] from ''[[Star Wars]]''.\n* Dru (voiced by Steve Carell): Gru's charming, happy-go-lucky long-lost twin brother, who is also in the super-villain business. Dru looks just like his brother, only he has blonde hair and wears white attire. He is Lucy's brother-in-law and the adoptive uncle of Margo, Edith, and Agnes.\n* Marlena (voiced by [[Julie Andrews]]): Gru and Dru's mother. Her neglect of Gru's ambitions is identified among the main reasons why he became a supervillain. In the denouement of the first film, she admits to him that he is a better parent than she. Marlena later makes a silent cameo appearance in the second film at Gru and Lucy's wedding. In the third film, Marlena reveals to Gru that after she and Gru and Dru's father divorced, they promised to never see each other again and they each got to take one son with them, with Marlena saying that she got \"second pick\".\n* Fritz (voiced by [[Steve Coogan]]): Dru's courteous, well mannered butler who speaks with a British accent. He takes Gru, Lucy, and the girls to meet Dru at his mansion in Freedonia.\n* Silas Ramsbottom (voiced by [[Steve Coogan]]): Director of the Anti-Villain League in the second film. The Minions (and Gru) make fun of his surname. In the third film, he retires from the AVL and is replaced by Valerie Da Vinci as the new Director of the AVL.\n* Valerie Da Vinci (voiced by [[Jenny Slate]]): A ruthless member of the Anti-Villain League who replaces Silas Ramsbottom as Director in the third film. She fires Gru and Lucy due to them failing to capture Balthazar Bratt, but rehires them in the end for capturing Bratt and returning the diamond, though it was not seen, but Gru imagines her rehiring him along with Lucy.\n\n===Antagonists===\n* Victor \"Vector\" Perkins (voiced by [[Jason Segel]], Jason Harris in the video game): In the first film, Gru's rival, and the son of Mr. Perkins, the President of the Bank of Evil that supplies loans to villains in their schemes (formerly including Gru). \n* Mr. Perkins (voiced by [[Will Arnett]]): The enormous and equally strong President of the Bank of Evil, responsible for giving out loans to villains in their schemes.\n* Miss Hattie (voiced by [[Kristen Wiig]]): The charismatic but cruel owner of the orphanage from which Gru adopts his daughters. She sends Margo, Edith, and Agnes out to sell cookies and makes them sleep in cardboard boxes if they fail to meet their quota.\n* Eduardo \"El Macho\" Perez (voiced by [[Benjamin Bratt]]): A Mexican-accented supervillain in the second film. As El Macho, he was believed to have died after strapping 250 pounds of TNT on himself and riding a shark into an active volcano. However, it turns out that he actually faked his death, and he became the owner of a Mexican restaurant. He has a son named Antonio, with whom Margo is infatuated at first, until Antonio abandons her. It turns out that Eduardo was aware of Gru's life as a villain and plans to abduct  most of Gru's minions and turn them into hairy, purple, savage, evil minions with a dangerous chemical compound he stole called PX-41 and send the mutated Minions to major cities to take over the world. In the final battle, as Gru manages to restore the mutated Minions to normal, Eduardo drinks the compound himself, turning into a big purple furry monster to fight Gru. He is defeated by Gru and Nefario.\n* Balthazar Bratt (voiced by [[Trey Parker]]): A supervillain in the [[Despicable Me 3|third film]]. A former 1980s child star, he adopts the identity of his supervillain character after the onset of puberty leads to the cancellation of his television series. He is obsessed with 1980s pop culture and uses a giant robot armed with a laser and inflatable bubble gum to exact revenge on Hollywood.\n* Clive (voiced by [[Andy Nyman]]): a robot who acts as Balthazar Bratt's sidekick.\n* Scarlet Overkill (voiced by [[Sandra Bullock]]): In ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]'', she is the world's first female super-villain who is bent on world domination.\n* Herb Overkill (voiced by [[Jon Hamm]]): Scarlet's husband and an inventor.\n\n==Chronology==\n* <small>''[[#Cro Minion (2015)|Cro Minion]]'' (2015)</small>\n* '''''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''''' (2015)\n* <small>''[[#Binky Nelson Unpacified (2015)|Binky Nelson Unpacified]]'' (2015)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Competition (2015)|Competition]]'' (2015)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Orientation Day (2010)|Orientation Day]]'' (2010)</small>\n* '''''[[Despicable Me]]''''' (2010)\n* <small>''[[#Home Makeover (2010)|Home Makeover]]'' (2010)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Banana (2010)|Banana]]'' (2010)</small>\n* <small>''[[Despicable Me Minion Mayhem]]'' (2012)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Puppy (2013)|Puppy]]'' (2013)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Training Wheels (2013)|Training Wheels]]'' (2013)</small>\n* '''''[[Despicable Me 2]]''''' (2013)\n* <small>''[[#Panic in the Mailroom (2013)|Panic in the Mailroom]]'' (2013)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Mower Minions (2016)|Mower Minions]]'' (2016)</small>\n* '''''[[Despicable Me 3]]''''' (2017)\n* <small>''[[#The Secret Life of Kyle|The Secret Life of Kyle]]'' (2017)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Yellow is the New Black (2018)|Yellow is the New Black]]'' (2018)</small>\n* <small>''[[#Minion Scouts (2019)|Minion Scouts]]'' (2019)</small>\n\n==Cast==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:10%;\"| Characters\n! colspan=\"3\" | Main films\n! Attraction\n! colspan=\"2\" | Spin-off films\n|-\n! ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 2]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 3]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me Minion Mayhem]]''\n! ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''\n! ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''\n|-\n! 2010\n! 2013\n! 2017\n! 2012\n! 2015\n! 2020\n|-\n! Felonious Gru\n| colspan=\"6\" | [[Steve Carell]]\n|-\n! Margo\n| colspan=\"4\" | [[Miranda Cosgrove]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Edith\n| colspan=\"4\" | [[Dana Gaier]]\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Agnes\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Elsie Fisher]]\n| Nev Scharrel\n| Elsie Fisher\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Dr. Nefario\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Russell Brand]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{N/A|''Silent cameo''}}\n| Russell Brand\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | [[Minions (Despicable Me)|Minions]]\n| [[Pierre Coffin]]<br>{{small|