d3d3;\" |\n| [[Sandra Bullock]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Herb Overkill\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jon Hamm]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! [[Elizabeth II|Queen Elizabeth II]]\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jennifer Saunders]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Walter Nelson\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Michael Keaton]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Madge Nelson\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Allison Janney]]\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n|-\n! Belle Bottom\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Taraji P. Henson]]\n|-\n! Jean Clawed\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Jean-Claude Van Damme]]\n|-\n! Nunchuck\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Lucy Lawless]]\n|-\n! Svengeance\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Dolph Lundgren]]\n|-\n! Stronghold\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Danny Trejo]]\n|-\n! Wild Knuckles\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Alan Arkin]]\n|-\n! Master Chow\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[Michelle Yeoh]]\n|-\n! TBA\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\" |\n| [[RZA]]\n|}\n* '''Note:''' A grey indicates that the character does not appear in that medium.\n\n==Crew==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" \"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | Role\n! colspan=\"3\" | Main films\n! colspan=\"2\" | Spin-offs\n|-\n! ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 2]]''\n! ''[[Despicable Me 3]]''\n! ''[[Minions (film)|Minions]]''\n! ''[[Minions: The Rise of Gru]]''\n|-\n! 2010\n! 2013\n! 2017\n! 2015\n! 2020\n|-\n! Director(s)\n| colspan=\"2\" |  [[Chris Renaud (animator)|Chris Renaud]] and [[Pierre Coffin]]\n| Pierre Coffin, [[Kyle Balda]] and Eric Guillon\n| Pierre Coffin and Kyle Balda\n| Kyle Balda, Brad Ableson and Jonathan del Val<ref name=Minions2Crew />\n|-\n! Producer(s)\n| [[Chris Meledandri]], John Cohen and [[Janet Healy]]\n| colspan=\"3\" | Chris Meledandri and Janet Healy\n|Chris Meledandri, Janet Healy and Chris Renaud\n|-\n! Executive Producer(s)\n| [[Sergio Pablos]] and Nina Rappaport\n| Robert Taylor\n| colspan=\"2\" | Chris Renaud\n| Pierre Coffin\n|-\n! Writer(s)\n| {{small|Screenplay:}}<br />Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio<br />{{small|Story:}}<br />Sergio Pablos\n| colspan=\"2\" | Cinco Paul and Ken Daurio\n| colspan=\"1\" | [[Brian Lynch (writer)|Brian Lynch]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Matthew Fogel\n|-\n! Composer(s)\n| colspan=\"3\" | [[Heitor Pereira]]<br />{{small|Original Songs and Themes by:}}<br />[[Pharrell Williams]]\n| colspan=\"2\" | Heitor Pereira\n|-\n! Editor(s)\n| Pamela Ziegenhagen-Shefland and Gregory Perler\n| Gregory Perler\n| colspan=\"3\" | Claire Dodgson\n|}\n\n==Film reception==\n{{details|Despicable Me#Reception|Despicable Me  2#Reception|Minions (film)#Reception|Despicable Me 3#Reception|topic=the reception of each film}}\n\n===Box office performance===\nThe film series has grossed a total of more than $3.7 billion, with an average of over $927 million per film,<ref name=\"BOMDM\" /> making the ''Despicable Me'' franchise the [[List of highest-grossing animated films#Highest-grossing animated franchises and film series|highest-grossing animated film franchise]], and the 15th [[List of highest-grossing films#Highest-grossing franchises and film series|highest-grossing film franchise]] of all time.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"width:99%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"3\" | Box office revenue\n! colspan=\"2\" text=\"wrap\" | Box office ranking\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! North America\n! Other territories\n! Worldwide\n! All time<br />North America\n! All time<br />worldwide\n|-\n| ''[[Despicable Me]]''\n| July 9, 2010\n| $251,513,985\n| $291,600,000\n| $543,11